{
  "id": 133205,
  "referenceId": 109259,
  "name": "Proverbs 31:1–9",
  "localizedName": "Proverbs 31:1–9",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In this section of the book of Proverbs, a mother speaks to her son. It isn’t known who King Lemuel was but his mother’s wisdom was from God. Some of her advice was like the father’s advice in Proverbs 1 – 9. She warned Lemuel about sexual sins."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Most of her advice was about how to rule wisely as "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108330",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "king"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Her advice agreed with God’s rules for kings in Deuteronomy 17:17–20. This included not having many wives. It included remembering what had been commanded. In Israel, this was the Law of Moses. Forgetting it led kings to treat others badly."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Instead, Lemuel was to protect and help poor and "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108418",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "needy people"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". This is described as speaking up for people who can’t speak up for themselves. As a leader, Lemuel had more authority than other people. He was to use this authority to take care of others and to be fair."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
